Job_description:
Top Prospect Group is working with a financial services firm looking for a Data Reporting Analyst to joint their team on a full-time basis.




Hybrid Work Environment - Norwalk, CT

$110-120k - Benefits

Oracle/SQL/Python/Unix




Job Responsibilities:

Document Application and data infrastructure
Lead effort to build out our Data Dictionary and Lineage
Make recommendations and optimize data for usage and quality based on findings
Work with teams to introduce AI and Machine learning concepts

Education/Skills/Experience:

Excellent working knowledge of Oracle
Data architecture and relational database design;
Excellent working knowledge of Oracle and SQL Server environments;
Solid Unix experience; file system navigation, file manipulation, and file transfer protocols;
Thorough understanding of data warehouse data models and concepts;
Excellent SQL performance tuning and data analysis skills;
Must have the ability to work independently and within a team;
Understanding of standard development life cycle processes;
Excellent communication skills and ability to develop strong relationships with stakeholder
Ability to communicate with various stakeholders to transform business requirements into technical implementation.
Bachelor level in Computer Science or equivalent experience;




Beneficial Experience:

Technical documentation;
Knowledge of banking and financial services;
Data partitioning and data archival processes;
Data Dictionary;
Quality Control;
Data conversion;
Business intelligence reporting;
